174. Whitewashing.– The roof and sides of the following places belowground in a mine shall be kept 
effectively whitewashed, namely:-   
(a) 
every shaft inset and shaft bottom or siding and every bye-pass which is in regular use; 
(b) 
the top and bottom of every haulage plane, every regular stopping place, siding, landing, 
pass-bye and junction, except within 100 meters of the face; 
(c) 
every travelling roadway;

