The shot-firer shall- 
(a) 
retain the key of the firing apparatus in his possession throughout his shift; 
(b) 
use a well-insulated cable of sufficient length to permit him to take proper shelter and in 
case of belowground working sufficient to take two right angle turns of pillar, and in no 
case, shall this cable be less than 50 meters in length;  
(c) 
before coupling the cable to the firing apparatus, couple up the cable himself to the 
detonator leads; 
(d) 
take care to prevent the cable from coming into contact with any power or lighting cable or 
other electrical apparatus; 
(e) 
take adequate precautions to protect electrical conductors and apparatus from injury; 
(f) 
himself couple the cable to the firing apparatus and before doing so, see that all persons in 
the vicinity have taken proper shelter as provided under regulation 196; 
(g) 
after firing the shots and before entering the place of firing, disconnect the cable from the 
firing apparatus. 
